  35:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** /**
  36:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   @ingroup groupFastMath
  37:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****  */
  38:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** 
  39:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** /**
  40:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   @defgroup cos Cosine
  41:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** 
  42:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   Computes the trigonometric cosine function using a combination of table lookup
  43:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   and linear interpolation.  There are separate functions for
  44:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   Q15, Q31, and floating-point data types.
  45:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   The input to the floating-point version is in radians while the
  46:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   fixed-point Q15 and Q31 have a scaled input with the range
  47:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   [0 +0.9999] mapping to [0 2*pi).  The fixed-point range is chosen so that a
  48:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   value of 2*pi wraps around to 0.
  49:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** 
  50:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   The implementation is based on table lookup using 512 values together with linear interpolation.
  51:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   The steps used are:
  52:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****    -# Calculation of the nearest integer table index
  53:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****    -# Compute the fractional portion (fract) of the table index.
  54:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****    -# The final result equals <code>(1.0f-fract)*a + fract*b;</code>
  55:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** 
  56:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   where
  57:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   <pre>
  58:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****      a = Table[index];
  59:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****      b = Table[index+1];
  60:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   </pre>
  61:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****  */
  62:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** 
  63:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c **** /**
  64:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FastMathFunctions/arm_cos_f32.c ****   @addtogroup cos
